When Dr. Ray Peat was in rural Mexico he was horrified how when the superstitious Mexican peasants who feared coldness accidentally got splashed with cold water at the end of a shower or forgot to close a window at night they would often proceed to actually fall sick with a cold.

Actual fever, unable to get out of bed, coughing, etc. and obviously for zero "real" reason. In some old school hospitals here in Bulgaria it's practice not to tell cancer patients they have cancer, we just lie to them about "a few weird cells that need to get removed surgically"

It's uncomfortable because at one point we're obviously dealing with something sitting a little outside the borders of conventional empirical science and closer to what The Wizard of Oz was doing with the silk heart stuffed of sawdust. So don't fear the cold as a concept too much
